===Etymology 1===
from [[Latin]] ''nonus'' ninth

===Noun===
'''nones'''
# In the [[w:Roman calendar|Roman calendar]] the eighth day ('''ninth''' counting [[inclusively]]) before the [[ides]] of a month. That is the seventh day of [[March]], [[May]], [[July]], [[October]], and the fifth day of the other [[month]]s.

